data.title: Join DFDS conference call for Q3 2025 update. Tune in for key financial figures and strategic insights.
data.description: In the latest report, it was revealed that the unemployment rate in the country has risen to 6.5% in the past quarter, marking an increase of 1.2% compared to the previous period. The number of job losses has also surged to 2.5 million, with the most significant impact seen in the manufacturing and hospitality sectors. Additionally, the report highlighted a decrease in GDP growth, which now stands at 2.1%, down from 3.5% in the previous quarter. Experts attribute these concerning figures to the ongoing economic challenges and disruptions caused by the global pandemic. The government has announced plans to implement various strategies to address the situation and stimulate economic recovery in the coming months.

data.title: monday.com named leader in 2025 Gartner® Magic Quadrant™ for Collaborative Work Management, 3rd time in a row; scored highest on Completeness of Vision and Ability to Execute.
data.description: In New York and Tel Aviv, Israel, monday.com (NASDAQ: MNDY) has been acknowledged as a Leader in the 2025 Gartner® Magic Quadrant™ for Collaborative Work Management (CWM) for the third year in a row. The company was ranked highest for both Completeness of Vision and Ability to Execute out of all vendors assessed in the 2025 report, marking the first instance of monday.com securing the top position on both axes in this evaluation. This recognition showcases the company's continued excellence in the field.

data.title: Wealth tax proposals spark debate globally amid soaring inequality; France divided over plan.
